Lexicon_Entry.ContributorNote: All subentries from 1m down are ready for level 5

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: = causative action by which human or deities produce an object, either personally or by others on behalf of them
= action by which humans or deities engage in a particular action
= action by which humans consult the spirits of deceased persons, either directly or through the intermediary of a professional; ≈ an activity forbidden in the law of Moses

Glosses.Gloss: to deal with spirits of the dead and mediums

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: literally: to be done; hence: = process by which certain events take place without observers always having a clear understanding of who is the agent
= causative action by which humans or deities cause events to take place without them having to necessarily be involved in the event itself
= causative action by which humans cause an event to happen to people or objects for a specific purpose
= causative action by which deities or humans in a position of authority establish a certain condition or pattern of events
literally: to do (something); hence: = action by which humans do what is needed for the benefit of other humans or parts of their body

literally: to do substantially; hence: = action as a result of which humans or deities are deemed worthy of respect, because of characteristics such as physical strength, power, bravery, skill, wealth, good character, or a combination thereof
literally: to make a name (for oneself); hence: = action as a result of which humans or deities gain a good reputation for themselves
literally: to make a name (for someone else); hence: = causative action by which deities provide humans with a good reputation

Glosses.Gloss: to make a name (for someone else)

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: literally: to do; hence; = action by which humans and engaged in a specific activity, usually in the service of someone else
literally: to make a house (for someone); hence: = causative action by which deities provide someone with a spouse and children
literally: to make a house (for someone); hence: = causative action by which deities provide humans with descendants over several generations
literally: to make (possessions); hence: = action by which humans obtain possessions
literally: to make (ready); hence: = causative action by which humans take an object and do what needs to be done to make it ready for a certain purpose
literally: to make (people in a certain role); hence: = causative action by which humans in authority or deities assign a certain task to (other) humans
literally: to make; hence: = natural process by which land, plants, or animals develop vegetation, branches, fruits, produce milk, etc.
literally: to make (plans); hence: = causative action by which humans or deities conceive events in their minds, ◄ described as an craftsperson producing an artifact
= action by which humans touch or stroke an object gently
